1
00:01:42,402 --> 00:01:47,647
Life is a bouquet of oranges,
bright and fresh

2
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:54,623
if sprinkled with laughter...
Plump with sweetness

3
00:01:56,683 --> 00:02:01,428
Each week passes
light-fooled and easy

4
00:02:02,889 --> 00:02:08,862
Each day dawns like
a Sunday morning

5
00:02:11,431 --> 00:02:14,776
Woven with threads of such joy

6
00:02:14,834 --> 00:02:17,906
Sparkles a story

7
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:21,419
its scent carried by the breeze

8
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:24,921
its melody whistled by the wind

9
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:44,532
In the white midday sun,
a golden spot of sunset

10
00:02:45,632 --> 00:02:51,548
No time for gloom,
we cherish every happiness

11
00:02:53,706 --> 00:02:58,416
Pockets full of small gestures
and big moments

12
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:06,092
No shroud of worry
we swirl in robes of content

13
00:03:08,121 --> 00:03:10,601
Woven with threads of this spirit

14
00:03:11,824 --> 00:03:14,896
Sparkles a story

15
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:18,075
its scent carried by the breeze

16
00:03:18,565 --> 00:03:21,444
its melody whistled by the wind

17
00:03:24,671 --> 00:03:26,651
Thank you for your help, sir

18
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:35,855
Life flows on

19
00:03:40,186 --> 00:03:43,497
Whispering a new-old song...

20
00:03:47,493 --> 00:03:49,700
In a blink and a sigh, I'm gone

21
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:57,641
Celebrate each moment,
together; hereon

22
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:01,177
Woven with threads of
our togetherness

23
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:04,621
Sparkles a story

24
00:04:05,178 --> 00:04:08,591
its scent carried by the breeze

25
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:10,988
Well fielded, Kayoze

26
00:04:11,618 --> 00:04:13,188
They say Catches win Matches

27
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,961
And Kayo's catch has certainly
turned the game around

28
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:17,132
Move

29
00:04:17,824 --> 00:04:20,031
Not out, sir

30
00:04:21,227 --> 00:04:23,036
My foot was on the line, sir

31
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:24,700
Sir, when I took the catch...

32
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:26,877
my foot was on the boundary line

33
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,279
C'mon guys, chin up

34
00:04:41,581 --> 00:04:43,720
Papa, you know how well
I played today?

35
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:44,927
I took 7 wickets

36
00:04:45,585 --> 00:04:47,724
You're listening, Papa?
- Listening, Kayo

37
00:04:48,087 --> 00:04:50,533
The ball was high but far

38
00:04:50,923 --> 00:04:52,766
Iran real fast to the ball...
and I dived

39
00:04:53,526 --> 00:04:55,096
Fantastic
- And catch

40
00:04:55,695 --> 00:04:56,730
Papa, that was a red light

41
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:57,900
Oh no

42
00:04:58,564 --> 00:05:00,669
Sorry son
- No Papa, I'm sorry

43
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:02,940
Do you see a traffic cop?

44
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,283
No Papa, no one

45
00:05:06,572 --> 00:05:08,745
How could you, Rusy...
I'm sorry

46
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:20,087
Bhau Waghmare'...
What sort of name is that?

47
00:05:20,186 --> 00:05:21,324
Good morning, sir

48
00:05:21,587 --> 00:05:22,258
Yes?

49
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:25,966
Sir, I ran a red light.
May I pay the fine please?

50
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:28,162
You didn't pay the
traffic cop there?

51
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:30,231
There wasn't anyone there

52
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:31,870
So who stopped you?

53
00:05:32,031 --> 00:05:32,873
No one stopped me

54
00:05:35,902 --> 00:05:38,314
You say you ran a red light

55
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:39,943
No cop there

56
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,745
So you should have left.
No big deal

57
00:05:43,609 --> 00:05:45,088
No one saw you

58
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:46,622
Someone saw me

59
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:47,722
Who saw you?

60
00:05:47,947 --> 00:05:49,324
My son saw me

61
00:05:51,284 --> 00:05:52,854
He will learn from what I do

62
00:05:53,219 --> 00:05:54,994
I ran a red light,
I must pay the fine

63
00:05:55,154 --> 00:05:58,067
Bylaw, I can't take your fine

64
00:05:58,224 --> 00:05:59,794
Please leave

65
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:03,932
Here's another headache

66
00:06:04,163 --> 00:06:08,043
Stop there.
Don't offload that car

67
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:09,268
C'mon, get the car down

68
00:06:09,635 --> 00:06:11,615
Inspector Mhatre, I told you...

69
00:06:11,738 --> 00:06:14,014
Don't tow any imported car
in this area

70
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:15,950
It could belong to a politician

71
00:06:16,342 --> 00:06:18,982
This car caused a
2 km long traffic jam

72
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:23,087
They park wrongly, we suffer

73
00:06:23,182 --> 00:06:24,752
Inspector Mhatre,
please listen to me

74
00:06:24,817 --> 00:06:28,026
One scratch on this car
means a big enquiry

75
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:29,725
Do you know how
expensive this car is?

76
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:31,698
Rs. 10.2 million -
cost in Mumbai

77
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,395
BMW 7 series, latest model

78
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:35,138
Sir, please take this fine

79
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:37,207
This is... '?
- The King of Honesty

80
00:06:37,363 --> 00:06:38,899
Meet the Champion of Truth

81
00:06:38,998 --> 00:06:40,204
One moment, sir

82
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,644
Remember?
- Of course!

83
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,775
Rustom Behram Deboo.
Head Clerk, Transport Office

84
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:49,920
Nandkumar Mhatre.
Inspector, Traffic

85
00:06:50,643 --> 00:06:54,648
And - my son
Kayoze Rustom Deboo

86
00:06:54,947 --> 00:06:56,688
Shinde, this man is amazing

87
00:06:56,983 --> 00:06:58,683
A boon for the traffic police

88
00:06:58,684 --> 00:06:59,719
Imagine that

89
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,857
He cleared that Ballard Pier jam
single-handedly

90
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:02,422
Wow

91
00:07:02,822 --> 00:07:03,664
Don't harass him

92
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:04,359
No, never

93
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:08,864
Here, let me gift you
these blank tickets

94
00:07:09,028 --> 00:07:12,009
Next time, write yourself a ticket

95
00:07:12,698 --> 00:07:14,177
Sir, take the fine please

96
00:07:14,233 --> 00:07:15,940
Shinde
- Got it, sir

97
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:18,174
Proud to meet you, Mr. Deboo

98
00:07:18,237 --> 00:07:19,307
Thank you, sir

99
00:07:21,741 --> 00:07:22,719
But sir...

100
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:24,114
What was your name now...

101
00:07:24,343 --> 00:07:29,019
Rustom Behram Deboo.
Head Clerk, Transport Office

102
00:08:00,913 --> 00:08:02,915
Rusy

103
00:08:03,182 --> 00:08:04,058
Yes Papa?

104
00:08:04,183 --> 00:08:06,129
Where are those noodles-shoodles?

105
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,128
Ready Papa, almost ready

106
00:08:08,287 --> 00:08:10,130
Grate some cheese over them

107
00:08:10,256 --> 00:08:11,257
Yes Papa

108
00:08:17,363 --> 00:08:19,343
Let's watch some cricket, Grandpa

109
00:08:20,766 --> 00:08:23,872
They're not cricketers,
they're salesmen

110
00:08:24,103 --> 00:08:26,276
They sell soaps and pomades

111
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:30,852
Ever heard of Don Bradman
selling fragrant hair gel?

112
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:33,247
Now buzz off, weasel

113
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:36,391
Always knocking that ball

114
00:08:38,484 --> 00:08:41,192
Papa, Grandpa is so mean

115
00:08:42,922 --> 00:08:44,833
Let it go Kayo, it's ok

116
00:08:45,324 --> 00:08:48,271
If he hates Indian cricketers,
why does he live in India?

117
00:08:49,262 --> 00:08:52,004
What's that, weasel?

118
00:08:52,064 --> 00:08:53,202
Nothing, Papa

119
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:56,145
Kayo, you don't speak
to your elders like that

120
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:58,380
Go, say sorry

121
00:09:00,439 --> 00:09:01,850
Kayo

122
00:09:05,878 --> 00:09:06,879
Sorry

123
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:13,087
Papa, your noodles

124
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:15,120
Too hot

125
00:09:15,121 --> 00:09:16,395
Sorry

126
00:09:16,923 --> 00:09:18,834
Added cheese?
- Yes Papa

127
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:20,268
Ginger and garlic?
- Yes Papa

128
00:09:20,459 --> 00:09:23,497
And Mr. Kayo,
here are your shoodles

129
00:09:32,972 --> 00:09:34,849
Last night I had a dream

130
00:09:35,341 --> 00:09:39,881
I was at Lord's, watching
the Cricket World Cup final

131
00:09:40,212 --> 00:09:42,089
India vs. Pakistan

132
00:09:43,849 --> 00:09:47,558
Last 2 overs, India needs
30 runs to win

133
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:49,858
At the non-striker end is
Sachin Tendulkar

134
00:09:50,056 --> 00:09:52,036
At the striker's end is...
Guess who, Kayo?

135
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:53,133
Guess...

136
00:09:53,392 --> 00:09:54,166
Kayo?

137
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,167
Give up?

138
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:58,841
At the striker's end is
Kayoze Rustom Deboo...

139
00:09:58,898 --> 00:10:01,105
Captain of the Indian Cricket team

140
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:03,907
Shoab Akhtar bowls at
5600 km/ hour

141
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:05,176
And Kayo easily flicks him...

142
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:08,241
That... was a wide ball

143
00:10:12,211 --> 00:10:13,281
Last ball now

144
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:15,923
6 runs to win

145
00:10:16,349 --> 00:10:18,192
All fielders at boundary

146
00:10:18,384 --> 00:10:19,384
Bowler runs

147
00:10:19,385 --> 00:10:20,864
Kayo lifts his bat up

148
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,196
Crowd chants...

149
00:10:22,355 --> 00:10:26,132
North, South, East, West...
Kayoze is the best

150
00:10:26,258 --> 00:10:30,934
Kayo... Kayo...

151
00:10:30,997 --> 00:10:34,069
Bowler bowls and
Kayo swings his bat

152
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:48,114
Of all the witless, idiotic...

153
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,064
Kayo

154
00:10:55,554 --> 00:10:59,024
Made the TV into a punching bag

155
00:11:00,092 --> 00:11:02,003
Were you batting or battering?

156
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,644
Kayo... Kayo...'

157
00:11:06,932 --> 00:11:09,572
Need a kick on your butt

158
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:12,981
I'm sorry, Kayo

159
00:11:13,572 --> 00:11:15,574
There's a match tomorrow.
What do I do?

160
00:11:15,941 --> 00:11:17,477
Sue him in the High Court

161
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:20,350
Now you'll say -
Look at the brighter side of life

162
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:22,586
Actually yes, Kayo

163
00:11:23,382 --> 00:11:25,555
What if it had broken
during the match?

164
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:29,166
Listen, we'll buy
a new bat tomorrow

165
00:11:30,289 --> 00:11:32,929
Remember the bat we'd
put a red mark on?

166
00:11:33,325 --> 00:11:35,032
We'll buy that

167
00:11:36,395 --> 00:11:39,137
But that's for Rs. 2800

168
00:11:39,632 --> 00:11:41,202
So what? I'll get it for you

169
00:11:42,568 --> 00:11:46,641
The match is at 9 am
but the shop opens at 9:30

170
00:11:47,306 --> 00:11:48,717
You play one down, right?

171
00:11:49,175 --> 00:11:51,052
I'll get it before your turn

172
00:11:52,478 --> 00:11:53,479
Are you sure?

173
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,384
Sure

174
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:55,389
One moment

175
00:11:58,084 --> 00:11:59,495
What're you looking at, Kayo?
- Nothing

176
00:12:00,619 --> 00:12:01,962
Shoes?
- No Papa

177
00:12:39,658 --> 00:12:46,769
Goodnight my angel,
now close your eyes

178
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:54,414
Goodnight love,
hush those sleepy sighs

179
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:58,483
Let the moon lull you

180
00:12:58,744 --> 00:13:02,351
into a gentle web of dreams

181
00:13:03,015 --> 00:13:06,360
As the night croons along with me

182
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,327
Goodnight

183
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:43,618
Excuse me, sir.
Does this shop open at 9130?

184
00:14:44,116 --> 00:14:45,754
That's what it says here

185
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:47,562
Don't know when it actually opens

186
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,792
Welcome, everyone, to the
Mumbai University Ground...

187
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:53,666
and the Young
Mumbai Indians Tournament

188
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,468
First ball of the innings

189
00:14:57,630 --> 00:15:00,406
And that's clean bowled.
Great delivery

190
00:15:00,766 --> 00:15:02,712
Next batsman is Kayoze...

191
00:15:02,768 --> 00:15:05,180
their captain and
their best batsman

192
00:15:05,504 --> 00:15:06,380
Sahil, go

193
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:08,350
Sir?

194
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,282
Go, I said

195
00:15:12,244 --> 00:15:13,552
Captain, what's your batting order?

196
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:15,384
Sir, I'll go two down

197
00:15:21,487 --> 00:15:23,160
Slow down, you'll trip

198
00:15:23,289 --> 00:15:25,360
A few days back I was
here with my son

199
00:15:25,391 --> 00:15:27,701
We'd put a red mark
on a bat, remember?

200
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,932
Which bat?

201
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,307
There're 2000 bats here.
Where will you look?

202
00:15:32,865 --> 00:15:34,435
Howzzat?

203
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,946
Huge appeal. And the
umpire raises his finger

204
00:15:37,503 --> 00:15:38,208
Go, Kayo

205
00:15:38,337 --> 00:15:39,611
Ball's keeping low, watch it

206
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:42,480
PTVA score -
27 for 2 wickets

207
00:15:43,175 --> 00:15:45,519
Sir, my bat broke yesterday

208
00:15:46,245 --> 00:15:47,417
So borrow one

209
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,294
But Papa's getting me a new bat

210
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,353
I'll go three down

211
00:15:54,186 --> 00:15:54,960
Nawaz

212
00:15:56,355 --> 00:15:57,663
I told you to keep that bat aside

213
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,261
Which bat? How will I know?

214
00:16:00,359 --> 00:16:01,838
Go look inside

215
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:03,362
Oh yes, there too

216
00:16:03,429 --> 00:16:04,669
Keep this
- What is it?

217
00:16:04,730 --> 00:16:05,708
Money

218
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:10,879
Now he'll attempt the impossible

219
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:17,944
An easy catch

220
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:21,315
PTVA score -
32 for 3 wickets

221
00:16:26,785 --> 00:16:28,492
That was close

222
00:16:28,887 --> 00:16:31,299
9... 10... 11 Found it?

223
00:16:31,357 --> 00:16:32,700
No, still looking

224
00:16:32,858 --> 00:16:34,769
It's not going to wait around
for so many days

225
00:16:40,866 --> 00:16:42,004
What now?

226
00:16:44,236 --> 00:16:45,510
Yes

227
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,750
Sir, if the next wicket falls
and Papa's still not here...

228
00:16:50,909 --> 00:16:52,252
I'll go to bat

229
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:53,652
OK

230
00:16:53,879 --> 00:16:54,721
Please hurry

231
00:16:54,813 --> 00:16:57,020
First you tire me,
then you hurry me

232
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:58,584
I'm sorry

233
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,998
How much for this,
after the discount?

234
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:04,858
If you give me 100 rupee bills,
then 1500 rupees

235
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:08,305
If you give me coins like this,
then 1700 rupees

236
00:17:12,464 --> 00:17:15,468
Right. I'll mark it.
Keep it aside

237
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,013
Next ball

238
00:17:17,403 --> 00:17:19,314
He tried to step out and play...

239
00:17:19,438 --> 00:17:20,644
and he's out

240
00:17:23,409 --> 00:17:25,013
Brilliant stumping

241
00:17:25,477 --> 00:17:26,615
Shut your mouth
- The over ends

242
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,289
Manmeet, bat

243
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:32,524
Sure?

244
00:17:36,655 --> 00:17:41,365
Kayo... Kayo...

245
00:17:45,364 --> 00:17:48,811
Finally on field is
Kayoze Rustom Deboo

246
00:17:49,301 --> 00:17:51,872
Score is 70 for 6 wickets.
Just 7 overs left

247
00:17:52,004 --> 00:17:55,315
They need 9 runs per over.
That's a tough one

248
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:59,413
But if there's Kayo,
there's hope for his team

249
00:18:04,683 --> 00:18:05,388
Next ball

250
00:18:06,018 --> 00:18:07,964
Ajinkya plays it superbly
to leg side

251
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:09,363
Could be 2 runs

252
00:18:10,522 --> 00:18:12,729
Kayo takes 1 run.
He's running for the 2nd

253
00:18:13,392 --> 00:18:14,427
He's running...
- Sir, 1 minute

254
00:18:14,493 --> 00:18:15,494
He's running...

255
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:16,705
Still running...

256
00:18:17,396 --> 00:18:19,000
He's just running...

257
00:18:19,398 --> 00:18:21,571
He's running off the field

258
00:18:35,013 --> 00:18:36,720
Quick Papa, please

259
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,596
Sorry I'm late, son
- it's ok, Papa

260
00:18:43,021 --> 00:18:45,558
Yes, this is it.
Bye Papa

261
00:18:45,824 --> 00:18:46,666
Kayo

262
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:47,937
One moment

263
00:18:48,494 --> 00:18:50,770
Wearing your guard?
- Papa, not here

264
00:18:50,863 --> 00:18:52,137
All the best
- Bye Papa

265
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:55,805
Here goes...

266
00:18:56,435 --> 00:18:57,470
He's off

267
00:18:57,903 --> 00:18:58,938
Watch now

268
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:00,514
All set

269
00:19:01,106 --> 00:19:02,551
All wired

270
00:19:03,075 --> 00:19:04,110
C'mon Kayo, hit

271
00:19:04,710 --> 00:19:05,620
All alert

272
00:19:06,111 --> 00:19:07,385
In position

273
00:19:07,746 --> 00:19:08,918
Revved to go...

274
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:10,822
In to battle

