547
00:36:45,903 --> 00:36:48,645
The glass damaged his cornea

548
00:36:49,173 --> 00:36:54,179
He was left with some vision,
but couldn't play cricket again

549
00:36:55,846 --> 00:36:57,689
And the other friend?

550
00:36:58,482 --> 00:37:00,120
He was selected to the Indian team

551
00:37:00,585 --> 00:37:03,930
Became rich and famous,
traveled the world

552
00:37:04,822 --> 00:37:07,132
He never came to meet his friend?

553
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:11,233
No, never

554
00:37:13,030 --> 00:37:15,135
Who's he, Papa?
Do I know him?

555
00:37:17,034 --> 00:37:18,206
Dharmadhikari

556
00:37:18,703 --> 00:37:20,205
Dilip Dharmadhikari?

557
00:37:21,739 --> 00:37:24,219
The world knows
D. N. Dharmadhikari

558
00:37:26,677 --> 00:37:27,655
But his friend...

559
00:37:30,214 --> 00:37:31,625
was forgotten long ago

560
00:37:32,817 --> 00:37:34,057
Where is he now, Papa?

561
00:37:45,196 --> 00:37:46,800
You're crying, Papa?

562
00:37:54,772 --> 00:37:56,217
He's in our living room

563
00:37:59,510 --> 00:38:00,648
Grandpa?

564
00:38:39,784 --> 00:38:40,854
Kayo?

565
00:38:41,852 --> 00:38:42,990
Was he the best?

566
00:38:43,988 --> 00:38:45,695
He was the bestest

567
00:39:06,877 --> 00:39:10,188
May this mind...

568
00:39:10,614 --> 00:39:15,154
its thoughts and deeds

569
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:20,063
Every stride and step

570
00:39:20,257 --> 00:39:24,933
Tread the path of Truth

571
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:30,005
Truth and Integrity . .

572
00:39:30,301 --> 00:39:34,977
Make for a tough path

573
00:39:35,239 --> 00:39:39,881
But remain fearless
and unwavering

574
00:39:40,144 --> 00:39:43,853
Always, with head held high

575
00:39:46,150 --> 00:39:49,825
Stand strong...

576
00:39:50,121 --> 00:39:54,763
On the tough, honest path

577
00:39:54,992 --> 00:39:59,771
Ana' remain fearless
and unwavering

578
00:39:59,964 --> 00:40:03,104
Always, with head held high

579
00:40:10,641 --> 00:40:14,179
...Lord's, London. So, I need a loan

580
00:40:16,814 --> 00:40:18,725
Sorry, not possible

581
00:40:35,833 --> 00:40:37,167
Good morning, ma'am
- Good morning

582
00:40:37,168 --> 00:40:39,035
I'd like to meet
a loan officer, please

583
00:40:39,036 --> 00:40:40,737
He's here

584
00:40:40,738 --> 00:40:41,805
Good morning, sir

585
00:40:41,806 --> 00:40:43,039
My name is Rustom Behram Deboo...

586
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:44,212
Head Clerk, Transport Office

587
00:40:44,241 --> 00:40:46,847
You didn't call me,
so I've come over

588
00:40:47,077 --> 00:40:48,021
I was going to call you?

589
00:40:48,312 --> 00:40:51,691
I have a new phone, you see.

590
00:40:52,049 --> 00:40:52,686
So?

591
00:40:52,750 --> 00:40:55,253
So I thought you'd call me
with a loan offer

592
00:40:55,719 --> 00:40:56,356
It's ok, sir

593
00:40:56,387 --> 00:40:58,833
Sir, my son,
Kayoze Rustom Deboo...

594
00:40:58,889 --> 00:41:00,256
is an outstanding cricketer

595
00:41:00,257 --> 00:41:02,134
He plays one down and
never returns to the pavilion

596
00:41:02,326 --> 00:41:04,397
He's been selected for
a cricket camp at Lord's

597
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,105
So, sir?

598
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:08,076
Sir, the camp's a bit expensive,
so I need a loan

599
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,968
Sir, one moment

600
00:41:10,067 --> 00:41:11,842
Sir, see Kayo's certificates

601
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:13,243
Sir, this is for Man of the Match

602
00:41:13,304 --> 00:41:14,771
This for Highest Scorer

603
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:16,183
Sir, for fielding too

604
00:41:16,273 --> 00:41:18,446
Sir, see his medals and trophies

605
00:41:18,709 --> 00:41:20,746
This is for Man of the Match

606
00:41:20,811 --> 00:41:23,724
This is for batting... fielding...

607
00:41:23,781 --> 00:41:26,387
One last thing
I want to show you, sir

608
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:31,229
His medals, sir

609
00:41:31,889 --> 00:41:33,368
Sir, if you see him play...

610
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:35,402
I'm sure you'll approve the loan

611
00:41:35,793 --> 00:41:37,170
Can I see your
salary slips, please?

612
00:41:37,261 --> 00:41:40,003
Yes, I have them here

613
00:41:43,234 --> 00:41:43,905
Transport Office?

614
00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:45,112
Head Clerk, sir

615
00:41:47,137 --> 00:41:48,047
How much money do you need?

616
00:41:48,439 --> 00:41:49,941
RS. 'I 50,000, Sir

617
00:41:51,242 --> 00:41:53,017
Sorry, you're not eligible
- I know that, sir

618
00:41:53,177 --> 00:41:54,815
You can't get a loan
on this salary

619
00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:55,448
I know that, sir

620
00:41:55,779 --> 00:41:57,759
Sir, that's why...

621
00:41:57,815 --> 00:42:00,159
I've got you his
certificates and trophies

622
00:42:00,217 --> 00:42:01,821
Sir, look at Kayo's talent

623
00:42:01,952 --> 00:42:03,761
OK, how much can I get
with my salary?

624
00:42:03,888 --> 00:42:04,764
135,000?

625
00:42:05,122 --> 00:42:06,260
125,0007

626
00:42:06,957 --> 00:42:11,194
Sir, if a father's salary is low,
can his son never move up?

627
00:42:11,195 --> 00:42:12,037
Please leave

628
00:42:12,096 --> 00:42:14,201
Why would anyone with
a fat salary want a loan?

629
00:42:14,431 --> 00:42:16,433
Only someone who has
less money will come to you

630
00:42:16,500 --> 00:42:17,200
Security

631
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:19,078
Sir, see his caliber and decide

632
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:21,149
Come to the club once
and see him bat

633
00:42:21,305 --> 00:42:22,477
Sir, he's wonderful

634
00:42:22,973 --> 00:42:23,508
Sir?

635
00:42:24,508 --> 00:42:25,350
Sir...

636
00:42:41,458 --> 00:42:43,563
Give him this. Tell him to
remember this name

637
00:42:43,894 --> 00:42:45,032
He'll be on TV some day

638
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:47,209
As he hits a sixer,
all of India will clap for him

639
00:42:47,264 --> 00:42:50,211
And your boss will smack
his head in frustration

640
00:42:51,335 --> 00:42:52,211
Have a good day

641
00:42:54,305 --> 00:42:57,081
Smack his head?
He'll crack his skull

642
00:42:57,408 --> 00:42:59,115
I tell you, Rusy...

643
00:42:59,276 --> 00:43:03,088
he'll suffer so much,
he'll commit suicide

644
00:43:03,914 --> 00:43:05,860
Don't stress. Don't let
this spoil your mood

645
00:43:06,016 --> 00:43:08,121
We'll find another way

646
00:43:09,954 --> 00:43:14,494
Mr. Kadam mentioned that
your father, Behram Deboo...

647
00:43:14,992 --> 00:43:16,869
played interstate cricket

648
00:43:17,127 --> 00:43:19,539
Yes, he was the youngest
interstate player

649
00:43:20,164 --> 00:43:23,475
That's wonderful

650
00:43:23,901 --> 00:43:25,608
Like grandfather, like grandson

651
00:43:26,503 --> 00:43:29,279
Cricket runs in your blood

652
00:43:30,207 --> 00:43:31,584
You didn't give it a shot?

653
00:43:32,142 --> 00:43:33,143
Actually, I...

654
00:43:33,177 --> 00:43:37,284
That's alright. Cricket's loss,
Transport Office's gain

655
00:43:39,049 --> 00:43:41,552
You know, relationships
don't mean anything today

656
00:43:42,086 --> 00:43:46,000
But one bond is still strong -
the bond of cricket

657
00:43:47,191 --> 00:43:49,467
It got me thinking

658
00:43:49,994 --> 00:43:54,101
Your papa can tell Sachin -
There's a family wedding

659
00:43:54,231 --> 00:43:57,041
Give me your Ferrari for 2 days

660
00:43:57,267 --> 00:43:59,543
How will Sachin refuse him?

661
00:44:01,939 --> 00:44:03,475
Papa won't...

662
00:44:03,907 --> 00:44:05,011
OK, imagine this

663
00:44:05,109 --> 00:44:07,248
Sachin asks your papa...

664
00:44:07,444 --> 00:44:09,390
Can I borrow Rusy's scooter
for 2 days?

665
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:11,585
Your papa will never refuse him

666
00:44:12,082 --> 00:44:14,255
That's the bond of cricket

667
00:44:14,418 --> 00:44:17,991
Yes, but Papa won't...

668
00:44:18,222 --> 00:44:21,101
OK now let me explain
what's in it for you

669
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:23,271
Come closer

670
00:44:24,294 --> 00:44:27,969
You speak to your papa...

671
00:44:28,232 --> 00:44:30,405
and get me Sachin's Ferrari
for 2 days

672
00:44:30,567 --> 00:44:33,548
In return, I'll give you
Rs. 150,000

673
00:44:33,937 --> 00:44:35,075
A gift, for you

674
00:44:35,406 --> 00:44:38,580
I'm a Government employee.
I can't accept gifts

675
00:44:39,009 --> 00:44:40,955
Ma'am, I've to leave now,
if you don't mind

676
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:43,450
Sorry, I've to go,
if you don't mind

677
00:44:47,184 --> 00:44:49,221
Our Kayo will go to London, Rusy

678
00:44:49,453 --> 00:44:50,363
Ma'am, what...

679
00:44:50,688 --> 00:44:52,031
Don't worry about it

680
00:44:52,189 --> 00:44:53,668
Go about your business

681
00:44:54,058 --> 00:44:56,060
Listen to me calmly

682
00:44:56,226 --> 00:44:58,103
You know the proverb...

683
00:44:58,295 --> 00:45:01,071
Opportunity knocks your door once'?

684
00:45:01,265 --> 00:45:03,370
Look, once this wedding's over...

685
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:05,346
you'll lose your chance of
sending Kayo to London

686
00:45:05,502 --> 00:45:07,607
I'm at your door, ringing the bell

687
00:45:08,005 --> 00:45:09,075
Ding dong

688
00:45:09,306 --> 00:45:11,149
But you've locked yourself in

689
00:45:11,341 --> 00:45:13,048
Unlock the door
- Look lady...

690
00:45:13,177 --> 00:45:14,679
Got a problem, Grandpa?

691
00:45:15,079 --> 00:45:16,524
There's a lady here

692
00:45:16,980 --> 00:45:19,051
Go on, now. Do your thing

693
00:45:19,249 --> 00:45:21,286
Open the door, let me in

694
00:45:21,385 --> 00:45:22,557
Take the Opportunity

695
00:45:22,686 --> 00:45:23,960
What do you say?

696
00:45:25,089 --> 00:45:26,067
Well?

697
00:45:27,624 --> 00:45:30,628
Ma'am, give me some time.
I'll talk to Papa

698
00:45:45,275 --> 00:45:47,118
Papa

699
00:45:47,511 --> 00:45:49,145
Sachin's making a century.
Come and see

700
00:45:49,146 --> 00:45:50,146
OK, in a while

701
00:45:50,147 --> 00:45:51,080
Now, Papa

702
00:45:51,081 --> 00:45:52,458
I have some work.
I'II join you, son

703
00:45:52,616 --> 00:45:53,526
Sixer

704
00:45:53,650 --> 00:45:55,061
Bye Papa. See you

705
00:46:00,157 --> 00:46:00,658
Hello?

706
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:03,636
Wrong number

707
00:46:04,628 --> 00:46:06,301
Hey Mr. Popular
- Yes?

708
00:46:06,396 --> 00:46:09,502
Your social circle's expanding.
Who was it?

709
00:46:09,566 --> 00:46:11,204
Wrong number, Papa

710
00:46:12,069 --> 00:46:13,673
You get dirty jokes or not?

711
00:46:14,404 --> 00:46:15,781
Wrong number, I said

712
00:46:16,473 --> 00:46:18,384
Always been a wrong number

713
00:46:24,548 --> 00:46:25,583
Hello?

714
00:46:31,722 --> 00:46:35,534
Babbu didi,
Sachin knows me very well

715
00:46:36,059 --> 00:46:38,767
Don't you worry, I'll handle it

716
00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:42,736
I will speak to Rusy

717
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:46,808
I'm his father,
he has to listen to me

718
00:46:50,808 --> 00:46:54,551
And when this is done,
you must visit us

719
00:46:55,045 --> 00:46:58,049
Yes, I'll speak to Rusy right away

720
00:46:58,282 --> 00:47:00,091
See you soon

721
00:47:02,252 --> 00:47:03,754
Rusy, you didn't tell me...

722
00:47:03,787 --> 00:47:06,461
you're getting Rs. 150,000
for Sachin's Ferrari

723
00:47:06,590 --> 00:47:07,728
No Papa, I told Babbu didi...

724
00:47:08,192 --> 00:47:12,140
Listen, don't you want Kayo
to be a cricketer?

725
00:47:13,797 --> 00:47:15,777
Pull up a chair. Sit down

726
00:47:16,099 --> 00:47:18,204
Listen carefully

727
00:47:19,736 --> 00:47:24,617
This is what you must do -
Go to Sachin's house and say...

728
00:47:25,142 --> 00:47:27,520
I am the son of Behram Deboo'

729
00:47:28,278 --> 00:47:29,313
You must understand...

730
00:47:29,580 --> 00:47:32,720
the bond of cricket is stronger
than any other bond

731
00:47:33,717 --> 00:47:35,424
Sachin doesn't drive
that car anyway

732
00:47:35,786 --> 00:47:38,665
It's rotting in his garage

733
00:47:44,127 --> 00:47:46,698
Papa, you're not fooling
with me, are you?

734
00:47:47,164 --> 00:47:49,667
Would I fool with you
on something like this?

735
00:47:50,267 --> 00:47:51,678
What's wrong with you?

736
00:47:53,604 --> 00:47:55,277
My dear Rustom...

737
00:49:23,727 --> 00:49:26,503
Good morning,
Mrs. Sachin Tendulkar

738
00:49:28,932 --> 00:49:30,912
How do I address her?

739
00:49:34,972 --> 00:49:37,782
Good morning, Mrs. Tendulkar

740
00:49:38,342 --> 00:49:40,288
Very good. Continue

741
00:49:40,444 --> 00:49:42,651
You know Tatiya Mandke,
the politician?

742
00:49:42,913 --> 00:49:44,290
His son's getting married

743
00:49:44,414 --> 00:49:47,554
For the wedding,
Tatiya wants his son to be in a...

744
00:49:48,352 --> 00:49:49,228
Ferrari

745
00:49:49,453 --> 00:49:50,693
What a fine idea

746
00:49:54,558 --> 00:49:55,901
He's a very caring father

747
00:49:56,226 --> 00:50:00,299
So I thought we could...
both... help him

748
00:50:00,564 --> 00:50:02,305
You see, you have 3-4 cars

749
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:03,709
If you can lend one of them...

750
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:05,279
like the Ferrari...

751
00:50:05,936 --> 00:50:09,713
say the Ferrari...

752
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:12,377
to Mr. Mandke for a few hours...

753
00:50:12,542 --> 00:50:14,510
he'll pay me Rs. 150,000 for it...

754
00:50:14,511 --> 00:50:17,014
and Kayo can go to Lord's

755
00:50:17,381 --> 00:50:19,327
Any chance, Mrs. Tendulkar?

756
00:50:19,449 --> 00:50:21,258
Very good. Smile

757
00:50:48,578 --> 00:50:48,988
Hello?

758
00:50:49,046 --> 00:50:50,286
Hello Rusy, any luck?

759
00:50:50,414 --> 00:50:53,588
You spoke to Papa?

760
00:50:54,317 --> 00:50:55,955
I have the Ferrari key
in my hand

761
00:50:56,787 --> 00:50:59,358
What? Seriously?

762
00:50:59,389 --> 00:51:00,026
You're a hero

763
00:51:00,290 --> 00:51:02,425
Actually, someone at the house...

764
00:51:02,426 --> 00:51:04,406
probably thought
I was the car cleaner

765
00:51:04,594 --> 00:51:06,665
Gave me all the car keys

766
00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:08,631
I haven't mentioned
the wedding yet

767
00:51:08,632 --> 00:51:10,433
I'll speak about it and call you

768
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:11,936
Wait, don't

769
00:51:12,335 --> 00:51:15,043
You got the car key
without asking for it

770
00:51:15,439 --> 00:51:16,611
It's a sign from above

771
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:19,548
Just take the car and come here

772
00:51:20,444 --> 00:51:21,577
What? No ma'am

773
00:51:21,578 --> 00:51:23,854
That would be stealing.
I can't do that

774
00:51:24,047 --> 00:51:25,583
Listen, do as I say

775
00:51:25,715 --> 00:51:26,989
No one will get to know

776
00:51:27,017 --> 00:51:28,792
It's a matter of a few hours

777
00:51:28,985 --> 00:51:31,761
Once the wedding's over,
we'll return the car

778
00:51:31,888 --> 00:51:33,663
I'm sorry ma'am,
I can't do this

779
00:51:33,824 --> 00:51:36,805
Rusy, think of your
son's potential

780
00:51:37,494 --> 00:51:39,496
He'll blossom at Lord's

781
00:51:39,896 --> 00:51:42,399
Sachin played for India
at the age of 16

782
00:51:42,566 --> 00:51:44,546
Your son will play at 12

783
00:51:44,701 --> 00:51:45,975
Youngest player ever

784
00:51:46,336 --> 00:51:49,408
Do your duty as a father

785
00:53:12,789 --> 00:53:16,965
Sir, the latest bestsellers

786
00:53:17,194 --> 00:53:18,172
No, thank you

787
00:53:18,528 --> 00:53:20,769
Hey, nice wheels

788
00:53:22,866 --> 00:53:24,675
No son, step back please

789
00:53:25,769 --> 00:53:27,680
No, don't do that

790
00:53:32,776 --> 00:53:34,983
Babbu didi, where should I
bring the Ferrari?

791
00:53:35,178 --> 00:53:38,682
You did it, my tiger

792
00:53:38,882 --> 00:53:40,122
This is great

793
00:53:41,218 --> 00:53:42,754
Come into the Worli village

794
00:53:42,852 --> 00:53:45,128
You'll see the
wedding festivities

795
00:53:45,522 --> 00:53:46,626
Drive towards them

796
00:53:46,690 --> 00:53:47,828
The Worli village?

797
00:53:47,991 --> 00:53:49,095
OK

798
00:53:56,533 --> 00:54:01,607
The turmeric ceremony
of our beloved Pakya

799
00:54:01,905 --> 00:54:02,975
Stop this

800
00:54:05,175 --> 00:54:06,916
Mr. Mandke

801
00:54:07,143 --> 00:54:11,250
Our Ferrari is coming hers

802
00:54:11,648 --> 00:54:14,822
Pakya, smile if you want
your photo taken

803
00:54:15,118 --> 00:54:16,825
560 horsepower

804
00:54:17,053 --> 00:54:22,002
Our Ferrari is coming hers

805
00:54:26,196 --> 00:54:27,800
What's the matter?

806
00:54:28,164 --> 00:54:31,509
Let the Ferrari turn around
and go back

807
00:54:32,969 --> 00:54:34,971
See what's written about me
in the paper

808
00:54:35,772 --> 00:54:37,718
Public coffers empty,
Tatiya has plenty'

809
00:54:38,141 --> 00:54:39,017
Oh no

810
00:54:39,109 --> 00:54:41,612
Page 5 today,
front page news tomorrow

811
00:54:41,711 --> 00:54:42,781
And that's the end of me

812
00:54:43,546 --> 00:54:44,616
As you know...

813
00:54:44,848 --> 00:54:49,524
there are more politicians
in prison than in power

814
00:54:53,857 --> 00:54:55,530
Now here's my idea

815
00:54:56,893 --> 00:54:58,930
I will tell the Press...

816
00:55:00,664 --> 00:55:03,167
I'm spending money...

817
00:55:03,867 --> 00:55:06,040
